<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Jonah on Christian Internet Resources</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/jonah/</link><description>Recent content in Jonah on Christian Internet Resources</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://christir.org/translations/cyv/jonah/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Jonah 1</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/jonah/chapter-01/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/jonah/chapter-01/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="jonah-chapter-1">Jonah Chapter 1&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="conversational-yahveh-covenant">Conversational Yahveh Covenant&lt;/h3>
&lt;h3 id="jonahs-flight-from-yahveh">Jonah’s Flight from Yahveh&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpFirst" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Yahveh told Jonah Ben-Amittai, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Go to Nineveh, that big city, and shout against it; I’ve seen how sinful they are.”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>But Jonah ran away. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He went down to Joppa, found a ship to Tarshish, paid the fare, and boarded.                                                     &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Yahveh hurled a gale on the sea, and it was about to break up the ship. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The sailors were scared, and every man cried out to his god. They threw the cargo overboard to lighten the ship. Jonah had gone below and fallen sound asleep. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v6" id="v6">&lt;sup class="verse-num">6&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The captain came and said, &lt;i>“How come you’re sleeping? Get up, call on your god. Maybe he’ll be concerned about us enough to keep us from dying.”&lt;/i> &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v7" id="v7">&lt;sup class="verse-num">7&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>They said to one another,&lt;i> “Let’s cast lots to find out who caused this catastrophe to hit us.” &lt;/i>They cast lots, and it fell on Jonah. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v8" id="v8">&lt;sup class="verse-num">8&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Tell us, now! Why has this catastrophe fallen on us? What’s your job? What’s your country? Who are your people?”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:10.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                                                     Jon 1:1-8&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Jonah 2</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/jonah/chapter-02/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/jonah/chapter-02/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="jonah-chapter-2">Jonah Chapter 2&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Jonah prayed to Yahveh his God from the fish’s stomach,&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            &lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“I called to you in my distress,&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                        and you answered me;&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                  I cried out for help from the belly of Sheol,&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                        and you heard me.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>You threw me into the deep, &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Jonah 3</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/jonah/chapter-03/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/jonah/chapter-03/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="jonah-chapter-3">Jonah Chapter 3&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="jonahs-trip-to-nineveh">Jonah’s Trip to Nineveh&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;a name="_Hlk122902941">&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;/a>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Yahveh told Jonah again, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Go to Nineveh, the big city, and deliver what I tell you.”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>So he went. It was a big city, a three-days’ walk-through. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He went through it one day’s walk and shouted, &lt;i>“&lt;/i>God&lt;i> is going to overthrow Nineveh in 40 days.” &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The people believed him. They called for a fast and put on burlap from least to greatest.&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Jonah 4</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/jonah/chapter-04/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/jonah/chapter-04/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="jonah-chapter-4">Jonah Chapter 4&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="jonahs-anger-over-yahvehs-mercy">Jonah’s Anger over Yahveh’s Mercy&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>That really made Jonah mad. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He told Yahveh, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“That’s exactly what I said back home and why I tried to run away to Tarshish. I knew you’re a gracious, merciful God, slow to get angry and full of enduring love, and relent from bringing catastrophe. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>So take my life; I’d be better off dead.” &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>